## Hypothesis
Enterprise Value to EBITDA (EV/EBITDA) is a widely used valuation metric that measures how expensive a company is relative to its operating earnings.

Lower EV/EBITDA indicates undervaluation, meaning the company generates higher earnings relative to its valuation.

By applying ts_zscore, we normalize the valuation across time, identifying relative extremes.

Using group_rank within industry ensures fair comparison across similar companies.

Thus, stocks with relatively low EV/EBITDA within their industry are expected to outperform.

---

## Alpha Expression
group_rank(-ts_zscore(enterprise_value/ebitda, 60), industry)

